def: One of several species of long-billed, wading birds of thegenus Limosa, and family Tringidæ. The European black-tailed godwit(Limosa limosa), the American marbled godwit (L. fedoa), theHudsonian godwit (L. hæmastica), and others, are valued as gamebirds. Called also godwin.
A special groove or furrow at one or both angles of the mouthof many Anthozoa.
Speaking reproachfully; slanderous. [Obs.] Sir E. Sandys.
Rubbish. Specifically: (a) Dross or refuse of metals. [Obs.](b) Light, dry wood, or stuff used for fuel. [Prov. Eng.]
The fruit of a trailing leguminous plant (Arachis hypogæa);also, the plant itself, which is widely cultivated for its fruit.
The hart in its second year; a young deer. [Written alsoknobber.] Halliwell.He has hallooed the hounds upon a velvet-headed knobbler. Sir W.Scott.
Having broad, loose, dependent ears. Shak.
A blusterer; a rowdy. [Obs.]Unpolished, a frapler, and base. B. Jonson.
